## Summary

**{{COMPANY_NAME}}** is **{{TODO_COMPANY_ONE_LINER}}**. This plan covers the next twelve months: where we want to be, what gets us there, what we need to get it done, and the risks that could knock us off course.

The plan is read by the team, by the board, and by anyone underwriting our growth (investors, lenders, grant bodies). It is updated at every board meeting.

## Product principles

1. The product earns the user's trust before it earns their money.
2. The simplest interface that works is the right interface.
3. Defaults are a feature; the right default removes a decision the user does not want to make.
4. Performance is part of the design. A slow product is a broken product.
5. Every error message tells the user what to do next.

## Repository layout

The repository is a pnpm monorepo. `apps/` holds deployable applications; `packages/` holds reusable libraries. Every package has its own `package.json`, its own `tsconfig.json`, and its own test command.

Cross-package imports go through the workspace alias (`@{{COMPANY_SLUG}}/<package>`). Files in `apps/*/src` may not import from a package's `/node` subpath unless the app explicitly opts in; the Biome rule enforces this.

## Review and updates

This document is reviewed at least annually, and whenever a change to the business or to the law makes it obsolete. The review owner is recorded in the *Domain and Account Register*.

Material changes are signed off by the board and recorded in the change log at the foot of this document.

